addict /ˈædɪkt/

(addicts) 

1. N-COUNT An addict is someone who takes harmful drugs and cannot stop taking them. (吸毒) 上瘾者 

例： He's only 24 years old and a drug addict. 他只有24岁，可已经是一个瘾君子。 

2. N-COUNT If you say that someone is an addict , you mean that they like a particular activity very much and spend as much time doing it as they can. 对…入迷的人 

例： She is a TV addict and watches as much as she can. 她是一个电视迷，看尽可能多的电视。

